    <div class="faq-grid">
      <div class="faq-left">
        <span class="label-pill">FAQ</span>
        <h2 class="h-md">Local citation tools, <span class="accent">answered.</span></h2>
        <p>Common questions from local business owners and agencies shopping citation tools. More? Email <a href="mailto:founder@thestacc.com">founder@thestacc.com</a>.</p>
        <p style="margin-top: 24px;">See more: <a href="/reviews/" class="accent">read tool reviews</a>, <a href="/alternatives/" class="accent">compare alternatives</a>, or <a href="/pricing/" class="accent">view pricing</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What are local citations and why do they matter?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Local citations are online mentions of your business name, address, and phone number (NAP) on directories, websites, and apps. Google uses citation consistency as a local ranking factor. Inconsistent data signals unreliability. Accurate, widespread citations strengthen your local search presence and help you rank in the map pack.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How many citations does a local business need?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">There's no magic number. What matters more is consistency and authority. A business with 50 accurate citations on high-authority directories will outrank one with 200 listings with conflicting data. Focus on the top 40–50 directories first — Google, Apple Maps, Bing, Facebook, Yelp, BBB, and industry-specific platforms.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the difference between citation building and listing management?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Citation building means submitting your business to directories where it doesn't yet appear. Listing management means keeping existing listings accurate and synced. Whitespark and Loganix specialize in building. Yext, Moz Local, and Synup specialize in management. BrightLocal audits both. Most businesses need some combination of each.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How long does it take for citation fixes to affect rankings?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Citation cleanup typically takes 4–8 weeks to propagate across directories. Some update within days; others take a month or longer. Google recrawls directory data on its own schedule. Most businesses see measurable local ranking improvements within 2–3 months of fixing major NAP inconsistencies.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I build citations myself for free?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. You can manually submit your business to each directory. This works but takes 15–20 hours to cover the top 50 directories. You also need to monitor them ongoing — directories sometimes revert data or create duplicates. Tools save time; manual work saves money.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do citation tools replace content creation for local SEO?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">No. Citations are one of 4 local ranking factors — alongside GBP activity, website content, and reviews. Fixing citations without publishing fresh blog content and GBP posts leaves 2 major ranking factors unaddressed. theStacc handles the content side at $49–$126/month bundled. Pair it with a citation tool for a complete local SEO approach.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What happens to my citations if I cancel Yext or Moz Local?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">With Yext, listings may revert to pre-Yext data when you cancel. Moz Local has similar reversion on some directories. Manually built citations (via Whitespark or Loganix) stay permanent. This is the most important consideration when choosing between automated sync tools and manual building services.</div>
        </div>
